  <steps>
    <step num="0">Preheat the oven to 425 °F (220°C). </step>
    <step num="1">In a large bowl, add the oats, almonds, cinnamon, salt, coconut oil, vanilla extract, maple syrup, and honey. </step>
    <step num="2">Mix until well combined. </step>
    <step num="3">Transfer the mixture onto a parchment paper-lined baking sheet and spread into an even layer. </step>
    <step num="4">Bake for 20 minutes. </step>
    <step num="5">Carefully remove and allow to cool for 10 minutes. </step>
    <step num="6">Break up the layer into chunks with your hands. </step>
    <step num="7">Store in an airtight container for up to one month. </step>
    <step num="8">Serve with Greek yogurt and fresh berries, if desired. </step>
    <step num="9">Enjoy! </step>
  </steps>
